{
  "stem": "19923.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That's the Yiddish word for-- for whip.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it actually was a cat of nine tails.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It had nine leather throngs on it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my older brother used to say, and when the teacher wasn't looking, you'd get a razor blade and cut off one at a time, hoping that over a period of time, there wouldn't be many left.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But the point was that the [YIDDISH] was used to teach you how to learn Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was more or less enforced on you with the crack of a whip.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But that was the way Hebrew was taught in school during that period of time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "From my earliest recollections in Cologne, we could never mingle with Germans.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We always mingled with the people-- Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we lived in an area which was predominantly Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was what you would probably imagine to be similar to what Flatbush was like in the '40s if you remember or have any idea of Flatbush, Lower East Side New York.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was a similar type of lifestyle-- pushcarts up the streets, people thronging about, a lot of Jewish people-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] --going back and forth.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But not too many Germans amongst them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And if the Germans did come, of course, and they came only for purposes of making trouble, but it was not that noticeable to us because it wasn't-- the Jewish people did not-- in Cologne, Germany wear the payoses and the-- the black clothing, black hats.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They didn't wear yarmulkes in public.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But you knew that from the people that you were acquainted with that they were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They would be-- I would say that would be more modern in dress, although the Germans always said in those days that you could tell a Jew by his nose.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
